President Trump delivered remarks on July 4th, 2018, at the South Lawn, where he celebrated American independence and honored the men and women of the United States Military. He was joined by Vice President Mike Pence and members of his Cabinet. The President emphasized that American freedom exists because of the brave Americans who are willing to defend it, and he recognized several individuals from the Army, Navy, Coast Guard, Air Force, and Marine Corps for their service and achievements. He expressed gratitude to all servicemembers and their families for keeping America safe, strong, proud, mighty, and free. The President concluded by wishing everyone a Happy 4th of July and asking God to bless America.